{
  "doc_id": "13839",
  "text": "It was Boltzmann who interpreted this concept statistically by inventing the infamous H -theorem [CITATION_1] , which then led to a new definition of entropy that makes use of the statistical weight of the macrostate; for a given macrostate, the Boltzmann entropy is defined as S B = ln Ω, where Ω is the number of constituent microstates. It is proportional to Clausius's entropy for systems in thermal equilibrium but is also meaningful for systems out of equilibrium, unlike the original definition of entropy [27] .",
